 <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody " xtrc="conbody:1;8:11" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">
  <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:1;9:6" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">In this scenario, a company with well-developed glossary wants to ensure that instances of a
   term that is defined in the glossary always include a link to the glossary topic.</p>
  <ol class="- topic/ol " xtrc="ol:1;11:7" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">
   <li class="- topic/li " xtrc="li:1;12:8" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:2;13:8" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">An information architect adds values for the <xmlatt class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlatt " xtrc="xmlatt:2;13:61" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">keys</xmlatt> attribute to all the of
     the <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:3;14:22" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">topicref</xmlelement> elements that are in the DITA map for the glossary, for
     example:</p>
    <codeblock class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xml:space="preserve" xtrc="codeblock:1;16:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">&lt;map&gt;
  &lt;title&gt;Company-wide glossary&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;topicref keys="term-1" href="term-1.dita"/&gt;
  &lt;topicref keys="term-2" href="term-2.dita"/&gt;
  &lt;topicref keys="term-3" href="term-3.dita"/&gt;
  &lt;topicref keys="term-4" href="term-4.dita"/&gt;
&lt;/map&gt;</codeblock>
   </li>
   <li class="- topic/li " xtrc="li:2;24:8" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:3;25:8" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">When authors refer to a term in a topic, they use the following mark-up:</p>
    <codeblock class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xml:space="preserve" xtrc="codeblock:2;26:16" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">&lt;term keyref="term-1"/&gt;</codeblock>
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:4;27:8" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">When the <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:4;27:29" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">term</xmlelement> element is rendered, the content <ph class="- topic/ph " xtrc="ph:1;27:84" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">is provided</ph>
     by the <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:5;28:25" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">title</xmlelement> element of the glossary topic. The
      <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:6;29:19" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">term</xmlelement> element <ph class="- topic/ph " xtrc="ph:2;29:50" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/example-keys-links-to-terms.dita">also is rendered as</ph> a
     link to the glossary topic.</p>
   </li>
  </ol>
